7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This file implements the LiveRange and LiveInterval classes. Given some ----
10 // numbering of each the machine instructions an interval [i, j) is said to be a ----
11 // live range for register v if there is no instruction with number j' >= j ----
12 // such that v is live at j' and there is no instruction with number i' < i such ----
13 // that v is live at i'. In this implementation ranges can have holes, ----
14 // i.e. a range might look like [1,20), [50,65), [1000,1001). Each ----
15 // individual segment is represented as an instance of LiveRange::Segment, ----
16 // and the whole range is represented as an instance of LiveRange. ----
17 // ----
18 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
19 ----

50 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
51 // Implementation of various methods necessary for calculation of live ranges. ----
52 // The implementation of the methods abstracts from the concrete type of the ----
53 // segment collection. ----
54 // ----
55 // Implementation of the class follows the Template design pattern. The base ----
56 // class contains generic algorithms that call collection-specific methods, ----
57 // which are provided in concrete subclasses. In order to avoid virtual calls ----
58 // these methods are provided by means of C++ template instantiation. ----
59 // The base class calls the methods of the subclass through method impl(), ----
60 // which casts 'this' pointer to the type of the subclass. ----
61 // ----
62 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

76 /// A counterpart of LiveRange::createDeadDef: Make sure the range has a ----
77 /// value defined at @p Def. ----
78 /// If @p ForVNI is null, and there is no value defined at @p Def, a new ----
79 /// value will be allocated using @p VNInfoAllocator. ----

81 /// either a pre-existing one, or the one newly created. ----

371 // overlaps - Return true if the intersection of the two live ranges is ----
372 // not empty. ----
373 // ----
374 // An example for overlaps(): ----
375 // ----
376 // 0: A = ... ----
377 // 4: B = ... ----
378 // 8: C = A + B ;; last use of A ----
379 // ----
380 // The live ranges should look like: ----
381 // ----
382 // A = [3, 11) ----
383 // B = [7, x) ----
384 // C = [11, y) ----
385 // ----
386 // A->overlaps(C) should return false since we want to be able to join ----
387 // A and C. ----
388 // ----
389 bool LiveRange::overlapsFrom(const LiveRange& other, 0
390 const_iterator StartPos) const { ----
391 assert(!empty() && "empty range"); 0
392 const_iterator i = begin(); 0
393 const_iterator ie = end(); 0
394 const_iterator j = StartPos; 0
395 const_iterator je = other.end(); 0
396 ----
397 assert((StartPos->start <= i->start || StartPos == other.begin()) && 0
398 StartPos != other.end() && "Bogus start position hint!"); ----
399 ----
400 if (i->start < j->start) { 0
401 i = std::upper_bound(i, ie, j->start); 0
402 if (i != begin()) --i; 0
403 } else if (j->start < i->start) { 0
404 ++StartPos; 0
405 if (StartPos != other.end() && StartPos->start <= i->start) { 0
406 assert(StartPos < other.end() && i < end()); 0
407 j = std::upper_bound(j, je, i->start); 0
408 if (j != other.begin()) --j; 0
409 } ----
410 } else { ----
411 return true; 0
412 } ----
413 ----
414 if (j == je) return false; 0
415 ----
416 while (i != ie) { 0
417 if (i->start > j->start) { 0
418 std::swap(i, j); 0
419 std::swap(ie, je); 0
420 } ----
421 ----
422 if (i->end > j->start) 0
423 return true; 0
424 ++i; 0
425 } ----
426 ----
427 return false; 0
428 } ----

471 /// overlaps - Return true if the live range overlaps an interval specified ----
472 /// by [Start, End). ----
473 bool LiveRange::overlaps(SlotIndex Start, SlotIndex End) const { 0
474 assert(Start < End && "Invalid range"); 0
475 const_iterator I = lower_bound(*this, End); 0
476 return I != begin() && (--I)->end > Start; 0
477 } ----

480 if (empty()) 0
481 return Other.empty(); 0
482 ----
483 const_iterator I = begin(); 0
484 for (const Segment &O : Other.segments) { 0
485 I = advanceTo(I, O.start); 0
486 if (I == end() || I->start > O.start) 0
487 return false; 0
488 ----
489 // Check adjacent live segments and see if we can get behind O.end. ----
490 while (I->end < O.end) { 0
491 const_iterator Last = I; 0
492 // Get next segment and abort if it was not adjacent. ----
493 ++I; 0
494 if (I == end() || Last->end != I->start) 0
495 return false; 0
496 } ----
497 } ----
498 return true; 0
499 } ----

502 /// (and any other deleted values neighboring it), otherwise mark it as ~1U so ----
503 /// it can be nuked later. ----
504 void LiveRange::markValNoForDeletion(VNInfo *ValNo) { 0
505 if (ValNo->id == getNumValNums()-1) { 0
506 do { ----
507 valnos.pop_back(); 0
508 } while (!valnos.empty() && valnos.back()->isUnused()); 0
509 } else { ----
510 ValNo->markUnused(); 0
511 } ----
512 } 0

524 VNI->id = (unsigned)valnos.size(); 0

566 /// Remove the specified segment from this range. Note that the segment must ----
567 /// be in a single Segment in its entirety. ----
568 void LiveRange::removeSegment(SlotIndex Start, SlotIndex End, 0
569 bool RemoveDeadValNo) { ----
570 // Find the Segment containing this span. ----
571 iterator I = find(Start); 0
572 assert(I != end() && "Segment is not in range!"); 0
573 assert(I->containsInterval(Start, End) 0
574 && "Segment is not entirely in range!"); ----
575 ----
576 // If the span we are removing is at the start of the Segment, adjust it. ----
577 VNInfo *ValNo = I->valno; 0
578 if (I->start == Start) { 0
579 if (I->end == End) { 0
580 segments.erase(I); // Removed the whole Segment. 0
581 ----
582 if (RemoveDeadValNo) 0
583 removeValNoIfDead(ValNo); 0
584 } else ----
585 I->start = End; 0
586 return; 0
587 } ----
588 ----
589 // Otherwise if the span we are removing is at the end of the Segment, ----
590 // adjust the other way. ----
591 if (I->end == End) { 0
592 I->end = Start; 0
593 return; 0
594 } ----
595 ----
596 // Otherwise, we are splitting the Segment into two pieces. ----
597 SlotIndex OldEnd = I->end; 0
598 I->end = Start; // Trim the old segment. 0
599 ----
600 // Insert the new one. ----
601 segments.insert(std::next(I), Segment(End, OldEnd, ValNo)); 0
602 } ----
603 ----
604 LiveRange::iterator LiveRange::removeSegment(iterator I, bool RemoveDeadValNo) { 0
605 VNInfo *ValNo = I->valno; 0
606 I = segments.erase(I); 0
607 if (RemoveDeadValNo) 0
608 removeValNoIfDead(ValNo); 0
609 return I; 0
610 } ----
611 ----
612 void LiveRange::removeValNoIfDead(VNInfo *ValNo) { 0
613 if (none_of(*this, [=](const Segment &S) { return S.valno == ValNo; })) 0
614 markValNoForDeletion(ValNo); 0
615 } 0
616 ----
617 /// removeValNo - Remove all the segments defined by the specified value#. ----
618 /// Also remove the value# from value# list. ----
619 void LiveRange::removeValNo(VNInfo *ValNo) { 0
620 if (empty()) return; 0
621 llvm::erase_if(segments, 0
622 [ValNo](const Segment &S) { return S.valno == ValNo; }); 0
623 // Now that ValNo is dead, remove it. ----
624 markValNoForDeletion(ValNo); 0
625 } ----
626 ----
627 void LiveRange::join(LiveRange &Other, 0
628 const int *LHSValNoAssignments, ----
629 const int *RHSValNoAssignments, ----
630 SmallVectorImpl &NewVNInfo) { ----
631 verify(); 0
632 ----
633 // Determine if any of our values are mapped. This is uncommon, so we want ----
634 // to avoid the range scan if not. ----
635 bool MustMapCurValNos = false; 0
636 unsigned NumVals = getNumValNums(); 0
637 unsigned NumNewVals = NewVNInfo.size(); 0
638 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVals; ++i) { 0
639 unsigned LHSValID = LHSValNoAssignments[i]; 0
640 if (i != LHSValID || 0
641 (NewVNInfo[LHSValID] && NewVNInfo[LHSValID] != getValNumInfo(i))) { 0
642 MustMapCurValNos = true; 0
643 break; 0
644 } ----
645 } ----
646 ----
647 // If we have to apply a mapping to our base range assignment, rewrite it now. ----
648 if (MustMapCurValNos && !empty()) { 0
649 // Map the first live range. ----
650 ----
651 iterator OutIt = begin(); 0
652 OutIt->valno = NewVNInfo[LHSValNoAssignments[OutIt->valno->id]]; 0
653 for (iterator I = std::next(OutIt), E = end(); I != E; ++I) { 0
654 VNInfo* nextValNo = NewVNInfo[LHSValNoAssignments[I->valno->id]]; 0
655 assert(nextValNo && "Huh?"); 0
656 ----
657 // If this live range has the same value # as its immediate predecessor, ----
658 // and if they are neighbors, remove one Segment. This happens when we ----
659 // have [0,4:0)[4,7:1) and map 0/1 onto the same value #. ----
660 if (OutIt->valno == nextValNo && OutIt->end == I->start) { 0
661 OutIt->end = I->end; 0
662 } else { ----
663 // Didn't merge. Move OutIt to the next segment, ----
664 ++OutIt; 0
665 OutIt->valno = nextValNo; 0
666 if (OutIt != I) { 0
667 OutIt->start = I->start; 0
668 OutIt->end = I->end; 0
669 } ----
670 } ----
671 } ----
672 // If we merge some segments, chop off the end. ----
673 ++OutIt; 0
674 segments.erase(OutIt, end()); 0
675 } ----
676 ----
677 // Rewrite Other values before changing the VNInfo ids. ----
678 // This can leave Other in an invalid state because we're not coalescing ----
679 // touching segments that now have identical values. That's OK since Other is ----
680 // not supposed to be valid after calling join(); ----
681 for (Segment &S : Other.segments) 0
682 S.valno = NewVNInfo[RHSValNoAssignments[S.valno->id]]; 0
683 ----
684 // Update val# info. Renumber them and make sure they all belong to this ----
685 // LiveRange now. Also remove dead val#'s. ----
686 unsigned NumValNos = 0; 0
687 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumNewVals; ++i) { 0
688 VNInfo *VNI = NewVNInfo[i]; 0
689 if (VNI) { 0
690 if (NumValNos >= NumVals) 0
691 valnos.push_back(VNI); 0
692 else ----
693 valnos[NumValNos] = VNI; 0
694 VNI->id = NumValNos++; // Renumber val#. 0
695 } ----
696 } ----
697 if (NumNewVals < NumVals) 0
698 valnos.resize(NumNewVals); // shrinkify 0
699 ----
700 // Okay, now insert the RHS live segments into the LHS. ----
701 LiveRangeUpdater Updater(this); 0
702 for (Segment &S : Other.segments) 0
703 Updater.add(S); 0
704 } 0
705 ----
706 /// Merge all of the segments in RHS into this live range as the specified ----
707 /// value number. The segments in RHS are allowed to overlap with segments in ----
708 /// the current range, but only if the overlapping segments have the ----
709 /// specified value number. ----
710 void LiveRange::MergeSegmentsInAsValue(const LiveRange &RHS, 0
711 VNInfo *LHSValNo) { ----
712 LiveRangeUpdater Updater(this); 0
713 for (const Segment &S : RHS.segments) 0
714 Updater.add(S.start, S.end, LHSValNo); 0
715 } 0
716 ----
717 /// MergeValueInAsValue - Merge all of the live segments of a specific val# ----
718 /// in RHS into this live range as the specified value number. ----
719 /// The segments in RHS are allowed to overlap with segments in the ----
720 /// current range, it will replace the value numbers of the overlaped ----
721 /// segments with the specified value number. ----
722 void LiveRange::MergeValueInAsValue(const LiveRange &RHS, 0
723 const VNInfo *RHSValNo, ----
724 VNInfo *LHSValNo) { ----
725 LiveRangeUpdater Updater(this); 0
726 for (const Segment &S : RHS.segments) 0
727 if (S.valno == RHSValNo) 0
728 Updater.add(S.start, S.end, LHSValNo); 0
729 } 0
730 ----
731 /// MergeValueNumberInto - This method is called when two value nubmers ----
732 /// are found to be equivalent. This eliminates V1, replacing all ----
733 /// segments with the V1 value number with the V2 value number. This can ----
734 /// cause merging of V1/V2 values numbers and compaction of the value space. ----
735 VNInfo *LiveRange::MergeValueNumberInto(VNInfo *V1, VNInfo *V2) { 0
736 assert(V1 != V2 && "Identical value#'s are always equivalent!"); 0
737 ----
738 // This code actually merges the (numerically) larger value number into the ----
739 // smaller value number, which is likely to allow us to compactify the value ----
740 // space. The only thing we have to be careful of is to preserve the ----
741 // instruction that defines the result value. ----
742 ----
743 // Make sure V2 is smaller than V1. ----
744 if (V1->id < V2->id) { 0
745 V1->copyFrom(*V2); 0
746 std::swap(V1, V2); 0
747 } ----
748 ----
749 // Merge V1 segments into V2. ----
750 for (iterator I = begin(); I != end(); ) { 0
751 iterator S = I++; 0
752 if (S->valno != V1) continue; // Not a V1 Segment. 0
753 ----
754 // Okay, we found a V1 live range. If it had a previous, touching, V2 live ----
755 // range, extend it. ----
756 if (S != begin()) { 0
757 iterator Prev = S-1; 0
758 if (Prev->valno == V2 && Prev->end == S->start) { 0
759 Prev->end = S->end; 0
760 ----
761 // Erase this live-range. ----
762 segments.erase(S); 0
763 I = Prev+1; 0
764 S = Prev; 0
765 } ----
766 } ----
767 ----
768 // Okay, now we have a V1 or V2 live range that is maximally merged forward. ----
769 // Ensure that it is a V2 live-range. ----
770 S->valno = V2; 0
771 ----
772 // If we can merge it into later V2 segments, do so now. We ignore any ----
773 // following V1 segments, as they will be merged in subsequent iterations ----
774 // of the loop. ----
775 if (I != end()) { 0
776 if (I->start == S->end && I->valno == V2) { 0
777 S->end = I->end; 0
778 segments.erase(I); 0
779 I = S+1; 0
780 } ----
781 } ----
782 } ----
783 ----
784 // Now that V1 is dead, remove it. ----
785 markValNoForDeletion(V1); 0
786 ----
787 return V2; 0
788 } ----

793 segments.empty() && ----

800 bool LiveRange::isLiveAtIndexes(ArrayRef Slots) const { 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
801 ArrayRef::iterator SlotI = Slots.begin(); 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
802 ArrayRef::iterator SlotE = Slots.end(); 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
803 ----
804 // If there are no regmask slots, we have nothing to search. ----
805 if (SlotI == SlotE) 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
806 return false; 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
807 ----
808 // Start our search at the first segment that ends after the first slot. ----
809 const_iterator SegmentI = find(*SlotI); 0
810 const_iterator SegmentE = end(); 0
811 ----
812 // If there are no segments that end after the first slot, we're done. ----
813 if (SegmentI == SegmentE) 0
814 return false; 0
815 ----
816 // Look for each slot in the live range. ----
817 for ( ; SlotI != SlotE; ++SlotI) { 0
818 // Go to the next segment that ends after the current slot. ----
819 // The slot may be within a hole in the range. ----
820 SegmentI = advanceTo(SegmentI, *SlotI); 0
821 if (SegmentI == SegmentE) 0
822 return false; 0
823 ----
824 // If this segment contains the slot, we're done. ----
825 if (SegmentI->contains(*SlotI)) 0
826 return true; 0
827 // Otherwise, look for the next slot. ----
828 } ----
829 ----
830 // We didn't find a segment containing any of the slots. ----
831 return false; 0
832 } ----

866 /// For each VNI in \p SR, check whether or not that value defines part ----
867 /// of the mask describe by \p LaneMask and if not, remove that value ----
868 /// from \p SR. ----
869 static void stripValuesNotDefiningMask(unsigned Reg, LiveInterval::SubRange &SR, 0
870 LaneBitmask LaneMask, ----
871 const SlotIndexes &Indexes, ----
872 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, ----
873 unsigned ComposeSubRegIdx) { ----
874 // Phys reg should not be tracked at subreg level. ----
875 // Same for noreg (Reg == 0). ----
876 if (!Register::isVirtualRegister(Reg) || !Reg) 0
877 return; 0
878 // Remove the values that don't define those lanes. ----
879 SmallVector ToBeRemoved; 0
880 for (VNInfo *VNI : SR.valnos) { 0
881 if (VNI->isUnused()) 0
882 continue; 0
883 // PHI definitions don't have MI attached, so there is nothing ----
884 // we can use to strip the VNI. ----
885 if (VNI->isPHIDef()) 0
886 continue; 0
887 const MachineInstr *MI = Indexes.getInstructionFromIndex(VNI->def); 0
888 assert(MI && "Cannot find the definition of a value"); 0
889 bool hasDef = false; 0
890 for (ConstMIBundleOperands MOI(*MI); MOI.isValid(); ++MOI) { 0
891 if (!MOI->isReg() || !MOI->isDef()) 0
892 continue; 0
893 if (MOI->getReg() != Reg) 0
894 continue; 0
895 LaneBitmask OrigMask = TRI.getSubRegIndexLaneMask(MOI->getSubReg()); 0
896 LaneBitmask ExpectedDefMask = ----
897 ComposeSubRegIdx ----
898 ? TRI.composeSubRegIndexLaneMask(ComposeSubRegIdx, OrigMask) 0
899 : OrigMask; 0
900 if ((ExpectedDefMask & LaneMask).none()) 0
901 continue; 0
902 hasDef = true; 0
903 break; 0
904 } ----
905 ----
906 if (!hasDef) 0
907 ToBeRemoved.push_back(VNI); 0
908 } ----
909 for (VNInfo *VNI : ToBeRemoved) 0
910 SR.removeValNo(VNI); 0
911 ----
912 // If the subrange is empty at this point, the MIR is invalid. Do not assert ----
913 // and let the verifier catch this case. ----
914 } 0
915 ----
916 void LiveInterval::refineSubRanges( 0
917 BumpPtrAllocator &Allocator, LaneBitmask LaneMask, ----
918 std::function Apply, ----
919 const SlotIndexes &Indexes, const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, ----
920 unsigned ComposeSubRegIdx) { ----
921 LaneBitmask ToApply = LaneMask; 0
922 for (SubRange &SR : subranges()) { 0
923 LaneBitmask SRMask = SR.LaneMask; 0
924 LaneBitmask Matching = SRMask & LaneMask; 0
925 if (Matching.none()) 0
926 continue; 0
927 ----
928 SubRange *MatchingRange; ----
929 if (SRMask == Matching) { 0
930 // The subrange fits (it does not cover bits outside \p LaneMask). ----
931 MatchingRange = &SR; 0
932 } else { ----
933 // We have to split the subrange into a matching and non-matching part. ----
934 // Reduce lanemask of existing lane to non-matching part. ----
935 SR.LaneMask = SRMask & ~Matching; 0
936 // Create a new subrange for the matching part ----
937 MatchingRange = createSubRangeFrom(Allocator, Matching, SR); 0
938 // Now that the subrange is split in half, make sure we ----
939 // only keep in the subranges the VNIs that touch the related half. ----
940 stripValuesNotDefiningMask(reg(), *MatchingRange, Matching, Indexes, TRI, 0
941 ComposeSubRegIdx); ----
942 stripValuesNotDefiningMask(reg(), SR, SR.LaneMask, Indexes, TRI, 0
943 ComposeSubRegIdx); ----
944 } ----
945 Apply(*MatchingRange); 0
946 ToApply &= ~Matching; 0
947 } ----
948 // Create a new subrange if there are uncovered bits left. ----
949 if (ToApply.any()) { 0
950 SubRange *NewRange = createSubRange(Allocator, ToApply); 0
951 Apply(*NewRange); 0
952 } ----
953 } 0

962 void LiveInterval::computeSubRangeUndefs(SmallVectorImpl &Undefs, 0
963 LaneBitmask LaneMask, ----
964 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, ----
965 const SlotIndexes &Indexes) const { ----
966 assert(reg().isVirtual()); 0
967 LaneBitmask VRegMask = MRI.getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(reg()); 0
968 assert((VRegMask & LaneMask).any()); 0
969 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI = *MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo(); 0

1071 void LiveInterval::verify(const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI) const { 0
1072 super::verify(); 0
1073 ----
1074 // Make sure SubRanges are fine and LaneMasks are disjunct. ----
1075 LaneBitmask Mask; 0
1076 LaneBitmask MaxMask = MRI != nullptr ? MRI->getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(reg()) 0
1077 : LaneBitmask::getAll(); 0
1078 for (const SubRange &SR : subranges()) { 0
1079 // Subrange lanemask should be disjunct to any previous subrange masks. ----
1080 assert((Mask & SR.LaneMask).none()); 0
1081 Mask |= SR.LaneMask; 0
1082 ----
1083 // subrange mask should not contained in maximum lane mask for the vreg. ----
1084 assert((Mask & ~MaxMask).none()); 0
1085 // empty subranges must be removed. ----
1086 assert(!SR.empty()); 0
1087 ----
1088 SR.verify(); 0
1089 // Main liverange should cover subrange. ----
1090 assert(covers(SR)); 0
1091 } ----
1092 } 0

1095 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1096 // LiveRangeUpdater class ----
1097 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1098 // ----
1099 // The LiveRangeUpdater class always maintains these invariants: ----
1100 // ----
1101 // - When LastStart is invalid, Spills is empty and the iterators are invalid. ----
1102 // This is the initial state, and the state created by flush(). ----
1103 // In this state, isDirty() returns false. ----
1104 // ----
1105 // Otherwise, segments are kept in three separate areas: ----
1106 // ----
1107 // 1. [begin; WriteI) at the front of LR. ----
1108 // 2. [ReadI; end) at the back of LR. ----
1109 // 3. Spills. ----
1110 // ----
1111 // - LR.begin() <= WriteI <= ReadI <= LR.end(). ----
1112 // - Segments in all three areas are fully ordered and coalesced. ----
1113 // - Segments in area 1 precede and can't coalesce with segments in area 2. ----
1114 // - Segments in Spills precede and can't coalesce with segments in area 2. ----
1115 // - No coalescing is possible between segments in Spills and segments in area ----
1116 // 1, and there are no overlapping segments. ----
1117 // ----
1118 // The segments in Spills are not ordered with respect to the segments in area ----
1119 // 1. They need to be merged. ----
1120 // ----
1121 // When they exist, Spills.back().start <= LastStart, ----
1122 // and WriteI[-1].start <= LastStart. ----
1123 ----
1124 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
1125 void LiveRangeUpdater::print(raw_ostream &OS) const { 0
1126 if (!isDirty()) { 0
1127 if (LR) 0
1128 OS << "Clean updater: " << *LR << '\n'; 0
1129 else ----
1130 OS << "Null updater.\n"; 0
1131 return; 0
1132 } ----
1133 assert(LR && "Can't have null LR in dirty updater."); 0
1134 OS << " updater with gap = " << (ReadI - WriteI) 0
1135 << ", last start = " << LastStart 0
1136 << ":\n Area 1:"; 0
1137 for (const auto &S : make_range(LR->begin(), WriteI)) 0
1138 OS << ' ' << S; 0
1139 OS << "\n Spills:"; 0
1140 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Spills.size(); I != E; ++I) 0
1141 OS << ' ' << Spills[I]; 0
1142 OS << "\n Area 2:"; 0
1143 for (const auto &S : make_range(ReadI, LR->end())) 0
1144 OS << ' ' << S; 0
1145 OS << '\n'; 0
1146 } ----
1147 ----
1148 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void LiveRangeUpdater::dump() const { 0
1149 print(errs()); 0
1150 } 0
1151 #endif ----
1152 ----
1153 // Determine if A and B should be coalesced. ----
1154 static inline bool coalescable(const LiveRange::Segment &A, 0
1155 const LiveRange::Segment &B) { ----
1156 assert(A.start <= B.start && "Unordered live segments."); 0
1157 if (A.end == B.start) 0
1158 return A.valno == B.valno; 0
1159 if (A.end < B.start) 0
1160 return false; 0
1161 assert(A.valno == B.valno && "Cannot overlap different values"); 0
1162 return true; 0
1163 } ----
1164 ----
1165 void LiveRangeUpdater::add(LiveRange::Segment Seg) { 0
1166 assert(LR && "Cannot add to a null destination"); 0
1167 ----
1168 // Fall back to the regular add method if the live range ----
1169 // is using the segment set instead of the segment vector. ----
1170 if (LR->segmentSet != nullptr) { 0
1171 LR->addSegmentToSet(Seg); 0
1172 return; 0
1173 } ----
1174 ----
1175 // Flush the state if Start moves backwards. ----
1176 if (!LastStart.isValid() || LastStart > Seg.start) { 0
1177 if (isDirty()) 0
1178 flush(); 0
1179 // This brings us to an uninitialized state. Reinitialize. ----
1180 assert(Spills.empty() && "Leftover spilled segments"); 0
1181 WriteI = ReadI = LR->begin(); 0
1182 } ----
1183 ----
1184 // Remember start for next time. ----
1185 LastStart = Seg.start; 0
1186 ----
1187 // Advance ReadI until it ends after Seg.start. ----
1188 LiveRange::iterator E = LR->end(); 0
1189 if (ReadI != E && ReadI->end <= Seg.start) { 0
1190 // First try to close the gap between WriteI and ReadI with spills. ----
1191 if (ReadI != WriteI) 0
1192 mergeSpills(); 0
1193 // Then advance ReadI. ----
1194 if (ReadI == WriteI) 0
1195 ReadI = WriteI = LR->find(Seg.start); 0
1196 else ----
1197 while (ReadI != E && ReadI->end <= Seg.start) 0
1198 *WriteI++ = *ReadI++; 0
1199 } ----
1200 ----
1201 assert(ReadI == E || ReadI->end > Seg.start); 0
1202 ----
1203 // Check if the ReadI segment begins early. ----
1204 if (ReadI != E && ReadI->start <= Seg.start) { 0
1205 assert(ReadI->valno == Seg.valno && "Cannot overlap different values"); 0
1206 // Bail if Seg is completely contained in ReadI. ----
1207 if (ReadI->end >= Seg.end) 0
1208 return; 0
1209 // Coalesce into Seg. ----
1210 Seg.start = ReadI->start; 0
1211 ++ReadI; 0
1212 } ----
1213 ----
1214 // Coalesce as much as possible from ReadI into Seg. ----
1215 while (ReadI != E && coalescable(Seg, *ReadI)) { 0
1216 Seg.end = std::max(Seg.end, ReadI->end); 0
1217 ++ReadI; 0
1218 } ----
1219 ----
1220 // Try coalescing Spills.back() into Seg. ----
1221 if (!Spills.empty() && coalescable(Spills.back(), Seg)) { 0
1222 Seg.start = Spills.back().start; 0
1223 Seg.end = std::max(Spills.back().end, Seg.end); 0
1224 Spills.pop_back(); 0
1225 } ----
1226 ----
1227 // Try coalescing Seg into WriteI[-1]. ----
1228 if (WriteI != LR->begin() && coalescable(WriteI[-1], Seg)) { 0
1229 WriteI[-1].end = std::max(WriteI[-1].end, Seg.end); 0
1230 return; 0
1231 } ----
1232 ----
1233 // Seg doesn't coalesce with anything, and needs to be inserted somewhere. ----
1234 if (WriteI != ReadI) { 0
1235 *WriteI++ = Seg; 0
1236 return; 0
1237 } ----
1238 ----
1239 // Finally, append to LR or Spills. ----
1240 if (WriteI == E) { 0
1241 LR->segments.push_back(Seg); 0
1242 WriteI = ReadI = LR->end(); 0
1243 } else ----
1244 Spills.push_back(Seg); 0
1245 } ----
1246 ----
1247 // Merge as many spilled segments as possible into the gap between WriteI ----
1248 // and ReadI. Advance WriteI to reflect the inserted instructions. ----
1249 void LiveRangeUpdater::mergeSpills() { 0
1250 // Perform a backwards merge of Spills and [SpillI;WriteI). ----
1251 size_t GapSize = ReadI - WriteI; 0
1252 size_t NumMoved = std::min(Spills.size(), GapSize); 0
1253 LiveRange::iterator Src = WriteI; 0
1254 LiveRange::iterator Dst = Src + NumMoved; 0
1255 LiveRange::iterator SpillSrc = Spills.end(); 0
1256 LiveRange::iterator B = LR->begin(); 0
1257 ----
1258 // This is the new WriteI position after merging spills. ----
1259 WriteI = Dst; 0
1260 ----
1261 // Now merge Src and Spills backwards. ----
1262 while (Src != Dst) { 0
1263 if (Src != B && Src[-1].start > SpillSrc[-1].start) 0
1264 *--Dst = *--Src; 0
1265 else ----
1266 *--Dst = *--SpillSrc; 0
1267 } ----
1268 assert(NumMoved == size_t(Spills.end() - SpillSrc)); 0
1269 Spills.erase(SpillSrc, Spills.end()); 0
1270 } 0
1271 ----
1272 void LiveRangeUpdater::flush() { 0
1273 if (!isDirty()) 0
1274 return; 0
1275 // Clear the dirty state. ----
1276 LastStart = SlotIndex(); 0
1277 ----
1278 assert(LR && "Cannot add to a null destination"); 0
1279 ----
1280 // Nothing to merge? ----
1281 if (Spills.empty()) { 0
1282 LR->segments.erase(WriteI, ReadI); 0
1283 LR->verify(); 0
1284 return; 0
1285 } ----
1286 ----
1287 // Resize the WriteI - ReadI gap to match Spills. ----
1288 size_t GapSize = ReadI - WriteI; 0
1289 if (GapSize < Spills.size()) { 0
1290 // The gap is too small. Make some room. ----
1291 size_t WritePos = WriteI - LR->begin(); 0
1292 LR->segments.insert(ReadI, Spills.size() - GapSize, LiveRange::Segment()); 0
1293 // This also invalidated ReadI, but it is recomputed below. ----
1294 WriteI = LR->begin() + WritePos; 0
1295 } else { ----
1296 // Shrink the gap if necessary. ----
1297 LR->segments.erase(WriteI + Spills.size(), ReadI); 0
1298 } ----
1299 ReadI = WriteI + Spills.size(); 0
1300 mergeSpills(); 0
1301 LR->verify(); 0
1302 } ----
1303 ----
1304 unsigned ConnectedVNInfoEqClasses::Classify(const LiveRange &LR) { 0
1305 // Create initial equivalence classes. ----
1306 EqClass.clear(); 0
1307 EqClass.grow(LR.getNumValNums()); 0
1308 ----
1309 const VNInfo *used = nullptr, *unused = nullptr; 0
1310 ----
1311 // Determine connections. ----
1312 for (const VNInfo *VNI : LR.valnos) { 0
1313 // Group all unused values into one class. ----
1314 if (VNI->isUnused()) { 0
1315 if (unused) 0
1316 EqClass.join(unused->id, VNI->id); 0
1317 unused = VNI; 0
1318 continue; 0
1319 } ----
1320 used = VNI; 0
1321 if (VNI->isPHIDef()) { 0
1322 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(VNI->def); 0
1323 assert(MBB && "Phi-def has no defining MBB"); 0
1324 // Connect to values live out of predecessors. ----
1325 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) 0
1326 if (const VNInfo *PVNI = LR.getVNInfoBefore(LIS.getMBBEndIdx(Pred))) 0
1327 EqClass.join(VNI->id, PVNI->id); 0
1328 } else { ----
1329 // Normal value defined by an instruction. Check for two-addr redef. ----
1330 // FIXME: This could be coincidental. Should we really check for a tied ----
1331 // operand constraint? ----
1332 // Note that VNI->def may be a use slot for an early clobber def. ----
1333 if (const VNInfo *UVNI = LR.getVNInfoBefore(VNI->def)) 0
1334 EqClass.join(VNI->id, UVNI->id); 0
1335 } ----
1336 } ----
1337 ----
1338 // Lump all the unused values in with the last used value. ----
1339 if (used && unused) 0
1340 EqClass.join(used->id, unused->id); 0
1341 ----
1342 EqClass.compress(); 0
1343 return EqClass.getNumClasses(); 0
1344 } ----
1345 ----
1346 void ConnectedVNInfoEqClasses::Distribute(LiveInterval &LI, LiveInterval *LIV[], 0
1347 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
1348 // Rewrite instructions. ----
1349 for (MachineOperand &MO : 0
1350 llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI.reg_operands(LI.reg()))) { 0
1351 MachineInstr *MI = MO.getParent(); 0
1352 const VNInfo *VNI; ----
1353 if (MI->isDebugValue()) { 0
1354 // DBG_VALUE instructions don't have slot indexes, so get the index of ----
1355 // the instruction before them. The value is defined there too. ----
1356 SlotIndex Idx = LIS.getSlotIndexes()->getIndexBefore(*MI); 0
1357 VNI = LI.Query(Idx).valueOut(); 0
1358 } else { ----
1359 SlotIndex Idx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*MI); 0
1360 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LI.Query(Idx); 0
1361 VNI = MO.readsReg() ? LRQ.valueIn() : LRQ.valueDefined(); 0
1362 } ----
1363 // In the case of an use that isn't tied to any def, VNI will be ----
1364 // NULL. If the use is tied to a def, VNI will be the defined value. ----
1365 if (!VNI) 0
1366 continue; 0
1367 if (unsigned EqClass = getEqClass(VNI)) 0
1368 MO.setReg(LIV[EqClass - 1]->reg()); 0
1369 } ----
1370 ----
1371 // Distribute subregister liveranges. ----
1372 if (LI.hasSubRanges()) { 0
1373 unsigned NumComponents = EqClass.getNumClasses(); 0
1374 SmallVector VNIMapping; 0
1375 SmallVector SubRanges; 0
1376 BumpPtrAllocator &Allocator = LIS.getVNInfoAllocator(); 0
1377 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &SR : LI.subranges()) { 0
1378 // Create new subranges in the split intervals and construct a mapping ----
1379 // for the VNInfos in the subrange. ----
1380 unsigned NumValNos = SR.valnos.size(); 0
1381 VNIMapping.clear(); 0
1382 VNIMapping.reserve(NumValNos); 0
1383 SubRanges.clear(); 0
1384 SubRanges.resize(NumComponents-1, nullptr); 0
1385 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumValNos; ++I) { 0
1386 const VNInfo &VNI = *SR.valnos[I]; 0
1387 unsigned ComponentNum; ----
1388 if (VNI.isUnused()) { 0
1389 ComponentNum = 0; 0
1390 } else { ----
1391 const VNInfo *MainRangeVNI = LI.getVNInfoAt(VNI.def); 0
1392 assert(MainRangeVNI != nullptr 0
1393 && "SubRange def must have corresponding main range def"); ----
1394 ComponentNum = getEqClass(MainRangeVNI); 0
1395 if (ComponentNum > 0 && SubRanges[ComponentNum-1] == nullptr) { 0
1396 SubRanges[ComponentNum-1] 0
1397 = LIV[ComponentNum-1]->createSubRange(Allocator, SR.LaneMask); 0
1398 } ----
1399 } ----
1400 VNIMapping.push_back(ComponentNum); 0
1401 } ----
1402 DistributeRange(SR, SubRanges.data(), VNIMapping); 0
1403 } ----
1404 LI.removeEmptySubRanges(); 0
1405 } 0
1406 ----
1407 // Distribute main liverange. ----
1408 DistributeRange(LI, LIV, EqClass); 0
1409 } 0
